    links: [
      { text: 'Tattoo studio software guide', url: '/tattoo-studio-software/' },
      { text: 'See pricing', url: '/pricing/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "How does MyTattoo compare to Booksy for tattoo artists?",
    answer: "Booksy is a booking marketplace popular with barbers and beauty professionals, and many tattoo artists use it for its discovery features. The trade-off is that Booksy is built around the beauty industry and its Boost feature takes a commission (around 30%) on the first booking from a new client who finds you through its marketplace — and it has no tattoo consent forms or reference image collection. MyTattoo.Software charges a flat monthly fee with no marketplace commission and includes tattoo-specific features Booksy doesn't.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Tattoo booking software', url: '/tattoo-booking-software/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Is Mindbody good for tattoo studios?",
    answer: "Mindbody is a powerful platform, but it's designed for fitness studios, spas, and wellness businesses. It's one of the most expensive options, the feature set is heavy for a tattoo studio, and it lacks tattoo-specific workflows like consent forms and reference uploads. For most tattoo studios it's more software than you need at a higher price than you'd want to pay.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Tattoo studio software', url: '/tattoo-studio-software/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Can I just use Square Appointments for my tattoo studio?",
    answer: "You can, and Square Appointments has a genuinely free tier plus solid payment processing. It works for basic scheduling and deposits, but it's a generic appointment tool — there's no tattoo consent form workflow and no reference image collection, and features like no-show protection sit on its paid tiers. It's a reasonable starting point, but you'll outgrow it as your studio's admin needs grow.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Compare features', url: '/tattoo-booking-software/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Why use tattoo-specific software instead of a generic booking tool?",
    answer: "Generic tools handle the calendar, but they don't understand how tattoo studios work. Tattoo-specific software collects reference images at booking, captures signed digital consent and medical-history forms, handles half-day and full-day sessions properly, and sets deposit policies that match industry norms. That removes the manual DM chains and paper forms that generic tools leave you managing yourself.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Tattoo studio software guide', url: '/tattoo-studio-software/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "How much does tattoo software cost?",
    answer: "Tattoo and booking platforms range from free to well over £150 per month. Square Appointments has a genuinely free tier; Booksy starts around £40/month for a solo artist plus marketplace commission on new-client bookings; Mindbody plans start around $99/month and commonly run higher. MyTattoo.Software is £29/month for solo artists and £79/month for studios up to five artists, with unlimited bookings and no per-booking or marketplace fees.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Full pricing details', url: '/pricing/' },
      { text: 'Start free trial', url: '/contact/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Which tattoo software is best for a solo artist?",
    answer: "For a solo artist, the priority is low cost, fast setup, and the tattoo-specific essentials: deposits, reminders, consent forms, and reference uploads. MyTattoo.Software's £29/month Solo Artist plan covers all of these with unlimited bookings. Square Appointments' free tier is a viable budget option if you're happy to manage consent forms and references separately.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Tattoo artist software', url: '/tattoo-artist-software/' },
      { text: 'See pricing', url: '/pricing/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Does switching tattoo software lose my existing bookings?",
    answer: "No. You can run the new system alongside your current one during the transition, pointing your Instagram bio link to the new booking page while existing appointments play out. Most studios switch over a single quiet week. MyTattoo.Software is designed to be set up in around 15 minutes so the changeover is low-risk.",
